5. EUROPEAN ECONOMIC AREA AND UNITED KINGDOM PRIVACY RIGHTS
Individuals located in certain countries, including the European Economic Area (EEA) and the United Kingdom (UK), have certain statutory rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) in relation to their personal data.
Data controller
Where we decide the means or purpose of processing your personal data, we are the “data controller."
Storage & Transfers
Where we use data processors outside the UK and EEA, and/or transfer personal data to a country which does not provide an adequate level of protection, we use contracts which give personal data the same protection it has in Europe and the UK. For more information drop us a line using the contact details at the “How do you contact us” section under the “Introduction” heading above.
Data Subject Access Requests
Please see the section entitled “What are your rights?” under the “Introduction” heading above.
Storage & Transfers
Please see the section entitled “How do you contact us?” under the “Introduction” heading above.
6. THE SERVICE AND CHILDREN
The VGX Products and Services are meant for adults age 18 years and above. We do not knowingly collect personal information from persons under 18. If you are a parent or legal guardian and think your child has given us information, you can contact us using the contact details at the “How do you contact us” section under the “Introduction” heading above.
7. SUPPLEMENTAL NOTICE TO RESIDENTS OF CALIFORNIA, VIRGINIA, COLORADO, CONNECTICUT, UTAH AND NEVADA
Depending on where you reside, you may also have additional legal rights with respect to your information. While some of these rights apply generally, certain rights apply in limited cases. Consistent with applicable laws, this Supplemental Notice provides a way to exercise such rights for residents of the above states.
Right to Know
You may have the right, depending on your jurisdiction, to request the following about the personal information we have collected about you during the past 12 months:
The categories and specific pieces of personal information we have collected about you;
The categories of sources from which we collected the personal information;
The business or commercial purpose for which we collected the personal information;
The categories of third parties with whom we shared the personal information;
The categories of personal information about you that we disclosed for a business purpose, and the categories of third parties to whom we disclosed that information for a business purpose;
The right to receive requested information in a readily-usable format if provided electronically; and
The right to update or correct any personal information which is out of date or incorrect.
To make a request, see the “How do you contact us” section under the “Introduction” heading above.
You may also have the right to ask if we disclose your personal information to third parties for their direct marketing purposes (we do not). It also gives you the right to ask if we sell your personal information to third parties (we do not, and have not done so in the past), and if we did (which we don’t), you would have the right to opt out of such sales.
Additional information about the categories of information we collect and its usage and sharing are located under the sections entitled “Your Data and How We Use It”, “Cookies, Analytics and Similar Technologies”, and “Data Retention and Disclosure”, above.
Right of Deletion
You have the right to ask us to delete the personal information we have collected from you, subject to exceptions the law provides. Please note that you may no longer be able to use the VGX Products and Services if you delete your personal information.
Right of Non-Discrimination
You have the right to not be discriminated against if you exercise these privacy rights. We will not discriminate against you, deny, charge different prices for, or provide a different quality of goods or services if you choose to exercise these rights.
How to Exercise Your Rights
If you live in a relevant jurisdiction and would like to send us a request to exercise one of your above rights, you may do so by contacting us as indicated in the “How do you contact us” section under the “Introduction” heading above.
To help protect your privacy and maintain security, we take steps to verify your identity before granting you access to your personal information or complying with your request.
You may designate an authorized agent to make a request on your behalf as permitted under law, though before we process that request, we will require that you provide the authorized agent written permission to do so and verify your identity directly with us.
To the extent permitted by applicable law, we may charge a reasonable fee to comply with your request.
Exceptions to These Rights
The law provides for certain exceptions to the rights described above. We reserve the right to avail ourselves of these exceptions where applicable.
8. SUPPLEMENTAL NOTICE TO VISITORS FROM OUTSIDE OF THE UNITED STATES
From time to time, some or all of our Properties or data collected in relation thereto may be hosted in the United States. By using our Properties, you acknowledge that your information may be transferred to, stored and processed in the United States in accordance with this Privacy and Cookie Policy and applicable U.S. laws. Please be aware that U.S. privacy laws, including the rights of authorities to access your personal information, may differ from those that apply in the country in which you reside.
9. “DO NOT TRACK” SIGNALS
Some websites have “do not track” features that allow you to tell a website not to track you. These features are not all uniform. We do not currently respond to those signals.
10. DATA SECURITY
We have put in place reasonable controls designed to help safeguard the personal data we collect via the VGX Products and Services. However, no security measures are perfect, and we cannot assure you that personal data that we collect will never be accessed or used in an unauthorized way.
